%N A099586 Constant term in (1+x)^n mod (1+x^4).
%C A099586 Equals real part of term (1,1) in M^n, where M = a 2 X 2 matrix [1,1; i,1], where i = sqrt(-1). - _Gary W. Adamson_, Mar 25 2009
%C A099586 {A099586, A099587, A099588, A099589} is the difference analog of the trigonometric functions {k_1(x), k_2(x), k_3(x), k_4(x)} of order 4.
%C A099586 For the definition, see [Erdelyi] and the Shevelev link. - _Vladimir Shevelev_, Jul 03 2017
%C A099586 a(n) = 0 if and only if n == 4 (mod 8). - _Robert Israel_, Jul 04 2017
%D A099586 A. Erdelyi, Higher Transcendental Functions, McGraw-Hill, 1955, Vol. 3, Chapter XVIII.
